{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17648616","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17648616"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:55:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:55:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18320"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18320","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18320"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.19,0.57,0.1,0.05,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11038"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74249"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11038","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11038"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18320"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59740"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"11273"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25614"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25620"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74249","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74249"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the histological changes in osteochondroma?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Necrotic bone with empty lacunae","Cartilage cap with disorganised chondrocytes","Fibrous stroma with giant cells","Osteoid matrix with woven bone","Dense fibrous tissue with calcification"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EOsteochondroma is a common benign bone tumour that typically arises near the growth plate of long bones. It is characterised by a bony projection covered with a cartilage cap.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe histological hallmark of osteochondroma is a \u003Cstrong\u003Ecartilage cap with disorganised chondrocytes\u003C/strong\u003E. The cartilage cap resembles the growth plate cartilage, and the chondrocytes are often arranged in a disorganised manner.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFibrous stroma with giant cells\u003C/strong\u003E - This is characteristic of giant cell tumour of bone\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOsteoid matrix with woven bone\u003C/strong\u003E - This is seen in osteoid osteoma\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENecrotic bone with empty lacunae\u003C/strong\u003E - This is typical of osteonecrosis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDense fibrous tissue with calcification\u003C/strong\u003E - This is seen in fibrous dysplasia\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOsteochondromas are benign and often asymptomatic, but they can cause mechanical symptoms or complications if they impinge on surrounding structures.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Osteochondroma is characterised by a cartilage-capped bony projection on the surface of bones.","The cartilage cap in osteochondroma resembles the growth plate cartilage.","Osteochondroma is a benign bone tumour that typically arises near the growth plate of long bones."],"references":["Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Mohan, H. (2018). Textbook of pathology. Jaypee Brothers Medical Publishers","Momodu II, Savaliya V. Osteomyelitis. [Updated 2023 May 31]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK532250/","Folpe, A., \u0026 Nielsen, G. P. (Eds.). (2022). Bone and Soft Tissue Pathology E-Book: A Volume in the Foundations in Diagnostic Pathology Series. Elsevier Health Sciences","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Ferguson, J. L., \u0026 Turner, S. P. (2018). Bone Cancer: Diagnosis and Treatment Principles. American family physician, 98(4), 205\u2013213."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59740"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18320"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59740","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59740"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-25T03:56:45+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-25T03:57:38+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11038"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74249"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving